# Security Scanning and Compliance
# ============================================================================

# Trivy/Checkov/tfsec output
trivy-*.json
checkov-*.json
tfsec-*.json
*.sarif

# ============================================================================
# Comments and Guidance
# ============================================================================

# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# 
# 1. NEVER commit *.tfstate files - they contain sensitive data including:
#    - Resource IDs
#    - IP addresses
#    - Potentially secrets and passwords
#
# 2. NEVER commit *.tfvars files - they often contain:
#    - Credentials
#    - API keys
#    - Passwords
#    - Private network information
#
# 3. Use terraform.tfvars.example as a template
#    - Keep it updated with required variables
#    - Document what values are needed
#    - Never include actual credentials
#
# 4. For team collaboration:
#    - Use remote state (Terraform Cloud, S3 with encryption)
#    - Use a secrets manager (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
#    - Never share credentials through version control
#
# 5. CSV files consideration:
#    - If your application-details.csv contains production IPs, consider excluding it
#    - Keep a sanitized sample file (application-details-sample.csv) for reference
#    - Document required CSV format in README

